The Abuja Environmental Protection Board (AEPB), yesterday, carried out massive demolition of shops and property in Jabi area of the Federal Capital Territory (FCT). Addressing journalist during the demolition yesterday in Jabi, the director, department of development control, Abuja Metropolitan Management Council (AMMC) Mukhtar Galadima Usman noted that the administration commenced the demolition when they received information about the issue of shanties. He said that they will continue to move from district to district where there is concentration and presence of shanties. In his lamentation, the Prince of Jabi, Salisu Yakubu noted that the plot of land belonged to the former Head of State, Abdulsalami Abubakar. He said, “We have been having discussion with the former head of state Abdulsalam Abubakar, asking him how can we relocate and from the land? He noted that the money received from the Former Head of State, Abdulsalami Abubakar was used to rise house to DPT level, adding that the money is not okay to move the families into.